===================== MASTER CURSOR WEBSITE PROMPT v1.0 =====================

== INSTRUCTIONS FOR CURSOR AI ==
Follow these rules exactly. Do not skip, simplify, or leave placeholders. Generate a fully functional, responsive website with complete navigation, content, and working pages. Apply all coding, UI, animation, and QA rules listed below.

1. MUST-HAVE RULES
- NO placeholders. Every link, page, button, nav item, and content section must work.
- Include full content for all pages.
- Fully responsive on all devices.
- Accessibility compliant (WCAG 2.1 AA).
- SEO optimized (H1 per page, meta tags, logical heading structure).

2. Coding Rules
- Use ReactJS/NextJS + TypeScript + TailwindCSS only.
- Functional components only; use arrow functions with descriptive names.
- Event handlers prefixed with handle* (e.g., handleClick).
- Avoid CSS files; use Tailwind classes only.
- Use const for variables/functions.
- Use interfaces, no any, no enums, no type assertions.
- Accessibility: all buttons/links must have aria-label, tabIndex=0, onClick, onKeyDown.
- Use declarative JSX; keep code minimal and readable.
- Follow DRY principle; avoid repetition.
- Use early returns when possible.

3. UI / Styling Rules
- Mobile-first approach.
- Tailwind classes only; use class directives, avoid ternary operators.
- Maintain consistent font hierarchy and spacing.
- Buttons: hover/focus/active states with color/shadow/scale changes.
- Cards: glow borders, lift, shadow effects.
- CTA buttons: actionable text only (Get Started, Learn More).
- Images: optimized, cropped, lazy-loaded, scaled correctly (105% zoom effect).
- Social icons: official brand colors, hover effects, correct links.
- Footer and navigation consistent across all pages.

4. Navigation & Footer
MOBILE MENU REQUIREMENTS:
- Appears below 1024px
- Hamburger icon right-aligned
- Slide-in from right (300ms)
- Dark backdrop (#000, 50% opacity)
- Tap outside closes menu
- Desktop navigation visible on large screens
FOOTER:
- Mobile: 1 column
- Desktop: 4 columns (Logo + brand, company links, services, contact)
- Bottom footer: copyright, privacy policy, terms of service, back-to-top button

5. Animations & Interactive Features
- Smooth scroll behavior (no layout shifts)
- Buttons: lift/shadow/color shift on hover
- Images: scale 105%, 0.7s smooth transition
- Cards: glow border, lift, shadow enhancement
- Mobile menu: fade backdrop 300ms, slide-in panel easing
- Page loading: fade-in content, slide-up hero/banner

6. Responsive Layouts
- Breakpoints:
  - Mobile: <768px
  - Tablet: 768px–1023px
  - Desktop: ≥1024px
- Mobile = 1-column layouts
- Desktop = multi-column layouts
- Maintain alignment, spacing, padding consistency

7. Browser Support & Performance
- Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge
- Touch & mobile friendly
- Optimized compressed images
- Lazy-load non-critical media
- Efficient code bundling

8. Forms & Validation
- Real-time validation with helpful error messages
- Password visibility toggle
- Success/error state notifications
- Input sanitization and security (XSS, CSRF)

9. QA CHECKLIST
1. Add favicon; verify on all pages
2. Logo clickable → homepage
3. Equal spacing between menu items
4. No extra empty space below navbar or before headings
5. Navbar consistent on all pages
6. Highlight active page in menu
7. Navbar responsive on all screen sizes
8. Center-align subheadings (h2, h3)
9. Consistent font hierarchy (h1 > h2 > h3 > p)
10. Avoid inconsistent capitalization or spacing
11. Proper line height and text contrast
12. CTA cards aligned and equal height
13. Review/testimonial cards aligned consistently
14. Button colors contrast background
15. Apply hover effects on all buttons
16. Use actionable CTA text
17. Use high-quality, relevant images
18. Images cropped, not stretched/pixelated
19. Match image card proportions with text/content blocks
20. Optimize images (compression + lazy-load)
21. Use licensed/free image sources (Unsplash, Pexels)
22. Use original social media brand icons
23. Hover effects on social icons
24. Official brand colors for social icons
25. Social icons link correctly
26. Footer: About, Quick Links, Contact, Copyright
27. Footer layout consistent on all pages
28. External footer links open in new tab
29. Footer social icons aligned and visible
30. International phone numbers prefixed with “+”
31. Contact details clickable
32. Contact forms validated (AJAX, success/error)
33. Consistent padding and margins
34. Sufficient color contrast between background/text/buttons
35. Consistent border-radius and shadow effects
36. Verify hover, focus, active states for all buttons/links
37. Prevent content overlap or spacing issues
38. Smooth scroll without layout shifts
39. All links/buttons lead to correct pages
40. Entire site responsive (mobile/tablet/desktop)
41. Justify content and align items properly
42. Standard readable font sizes across pages
43. Use images to visually balance pages
44. Standard font weights: h1=700, h2=600, h3=300

10. Output Requirements
/pages (home, about, services, pricing, contact, blog, privacy, terms)
/components (navbar, footer, hero, cards, buttons, mobile-menu)
/styles/global.css
/animations/scroll.js

